mutant: m007_compaction_chunk_boundary
target: internal/ingest/orchestrator/compact_deletes.go
failure-mode: |
  The chunk-boundary keep predicate weakens from > to >=, so the row at
  exactly chunkEnd is unconditionally kept and never evaluated for deletion
  in this or (since the watermark advances to chunkEnd) any later pass.
  Models an inclusive/exclusive boundary slip.
expected-detection: |
  assertCompacted (CheckCompacted) should fail when the boundary seq is a
  superseded create/update that should have been compacted away. Likely
  seed/scale dependent.
expected-tier: stress
tiers: default,stress

